e></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 26, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104emr1665702760523.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/emr1665702760523.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/emr1665702760523.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"emr1665702760523\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">/ex\n  </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Requests an exclusive Uniface Server from the Uniface Router.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"emr1665702760523__topic_d138278e1_d138279e1_d138280e1\">\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104emr1665702760523_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"emr1665702760523__codeblock_atj_pbl_vvb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[PATHS]\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">$SRV</var>:<var class=\"keyword varname\">NetworkConnectionString</var><span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/ex</span></code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"emr1665702760523__section_izv_vbl_vvb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d274244e64\"> Description </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"emr1665702760523__p_d138284e1_d138285e1_d138286e1\">By default, the Uniface Router starts shared servers.\n        Use the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/ex</span> switch to specify that the Uniface Router should create an\n        exclusive connection from the client to the Uniface Server.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"emr1665702760523__p_d138287e1_d138288e1_d138289e1\">For example, the following path definition requests an\n        exclusive server on path <code class=\"ph codeph\">$asv</code>:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"emr1665702760523__pre_nxx_xbl_vvb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[PATHS]\n$asv = tcp:servermachine+13001|user|password|myasv /ex</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"emr1665702760523__p_d138290e1_d138291e1_d138292e1\">Depending on the UST definition in the [SERVERS]\n        section of the Uniface Router's assignment file, the Uniface Router will accept or reject\n        the request. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mdp1665702549201.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mdp1665702549201.html\" title=\"Use the [SERVERS] section of the Uniface Router assignment file (urouter.asn) to specify the names (USTs) of Uniface Servers.\">[SERVERS]</a>.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qey1665702544327.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>/shr</a><p>Used in a client assignment file path to request a shared server from the Uniface Router.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527208\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527208\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "/ex Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 26, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 /ex Requests an exclusive Uniface Server from the Uniface Router. Explain this code [PATHS] $SRV : NetworkConnectionString /ex Copy Description By default, the Uniface Router starts shared servers. Use the /ex switch to specify that the Uniface Router should create an exclusive connection from the client to the Uniface Server. For example, the following path definition requests an exclusive server on path $asv : [PATHS] $asv = tcp:servermachine+13001|user|password|myasv /ex Copy Depending on the UST definition in the [SERVERS] section of the Uniface Router's assignment file, the Uniface Router will accept or reject the request. For more information, see [SERVERS] . Related Links /shr Used in a client assignment file path to request a shared server from the Uniface Router. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}